2134:\"<p>I hate politics.  I value honesty, morality, and personal responsibility, all of which seem to be overwhelmingly lacking in nearly every area of politics and law making.</p>\n<p>Having said all that, I still try to follow what&#8217;s going on.  Why?  Well, because I need to know what&#8217;s going on if I plan to vote, and how can I expect things to get better (or not get worse) if I won&#8217;t do anything about it.  The <a href=\"http://www.opencongress.org/bill/112-s968/show\">Protect IP Act</a> is a perfect example.  It needs to be stopped because it threatens our free speech and the internet as a whole.  The video below sums it up pretty well.</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/31100268\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>Go to <a href=\"http://fightforthefuture.org/pipa/\">Fight for the Future</a> and <a href=\"http://americancensorship.org/\">American Censorship</a> to send a message to congress.<br />\n<h3 class=\'related_post_title\'>Related Posts:</h3>\n<ul class=\'related_post\'>\n<li><a href=\'http://xavisys.com/speaking-at-wordcamp-san-francisco-2011/\' title=\'Speaking at WordCamp San Francisco 2011\'>Speaking at WordCamp San Francisco 2011</a></li>\n<li><a href=\'http://xavisys.com/press-release-xavisys-acquires-attackr-web-development-news-blogs/\' title=\'Press Release: Xavisys Acquires Attackr.com – Web Development News Blogs\'>Press Release: Xavisys Acquires Attackr.com – Web Development News Blogs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\'http://xavisys.com/becoming-a-freelance-web-developerdesigner/\' title=\'Becoming a Freelance Web Developer/Designer\'>Becoming a Freelance Web Developer/Designer</a></li>\n<li><a href=\'http://xavisys.com/new-web-development-resource-launched/\' title=\'New Web Development Resource Launched\'>New Web Development Resource Launched</a></li>\n<li><a href=\'http://xavisys.com/why-contribute-to-the-open-source-community/\' title=\'Why Con