	(115,1,'2011-11-29 00:42:21','2011-11-29 00:42:21','Here is a quick and solid way to add PHPUnit to your MAMP Setup\r\n<h3>Important:</h3>\r\nThe path to your PHP and PEAR if you are using MAMP is something similar to this\r\n<h4>PHP:</h4>\r\n<strong><code>/Applications/MAMP/bin/php/php5.xxx/bin/php</code></strong>\r\n<h4>PEAR:</h4>\r\n<strong><code>/Applications/MAMP/bin/php/php5.xxx/bin/pear</code></strong>\r\n\r\nnotice the <strong>php5.xxx</strong> this will depend on the version of php you are using, in my case is php5.3.6 so have that in mind if you are planning on copy pasting this guide\r\n\r\n<h2>Instructions:</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Turn on PEAR auto discover\r\n<strong><code>/Applications/MAMP/bin/php/php5.3.6/bin/pear config-set auto_discover 1</code></strong></li>\r\n	<li>Install PHPUnit from pear.phpunit.de\r\n<strong><code>/Applications/MAMP/bin/php/php5.3.6/bin/pear install pear.phpunit.de/PHPUnit</code></strong>This will install PHPUnit under\r\n<strong><code>/Applications/MAMP/bin/php/php5.3.6/bin/phpunit</code></strong></li>\r\n	<li>If done right the phpunit file should already contain reference to the MAMP\'s php you are choosing to use, now to have phpunit available on your system as a command you can do something similar to this:\r\n<strong><code>sudo ln -s /Applications/MAMP/bin/php/php5.3.6/bin/phpunit /usr/local/bin/phpunit</code></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI always try to keep my binaries and executables under <strong>/usr/local/bin</strong> but this is my choice you can try some other directory as long as you have it exposed on via your EXPORTS','Installing PHPUnit on OS X using MAMP via PEAR','','publish','open','open','','installing-phpunit-on-os-x-using-mamp-via-pear','','','2011-11-29 00:44:51','2011-11-29 00:44:51','',0,'http://rroche/?p=115',0,'post','',0),
